docs.abstract: Mr. Belzberg was a Canadian who, with his brothers, amassed a fortune using the “greenmail” takeover tactic and later reinvented himself as a private-equity investor.
docs.snippet: Mr. Belzberg was a Canadian who, with his brothers, amassed a fortune using the “greenmail” takeover tactic and later reinvented himself as a private-equity investor.
docs.lead_paragraph: Samuel Belzberg, a feared corporate raider of the 1980s who perfected the contentious practice known as greenmail to build one of Canada’s foremost family dynasties, then reinvented himself as a successful private-equity investor, died on Friday night in a hospital in Vancouver, British Columbia. He was 89.

headline.main: Samuel Belzberg, Corporate Raider in a Family Dynasty, Dies at 89
headline.print_headline: Samuel Belzberg, Corporate Raider  In a Family Dynasty, Is Dead at 89
